Polish Stocks: Grupa Lotos, KGHM Polska Miedz, PKN Orlen Move

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-06-20T13:57:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/polish-stocks-grupa-lotos-kghm-polska-miedz-pkn-orlen-move.html
Poland’s WIG20 Index retreated
27.82, or 1 percent, to 2,852.31 by 3:56 p.m. in Warsaw, heading
for the lowest close since June 10.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , Poland second-largest refiner,
lost 1.3 percent to 46.87 zloty. Oil fell to the lowest in four
months in New York, bringing its decline from this year’s peak
to 20 percent, on speculation a weakening global economy and
Greece’s debt crisis will lead to reduced fuel demand.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , Poland’s biggest copper
miner, slid 0.7 percent to 184.7 zloty, its third day of losses.
Copper for three-month delivery dropped $105, or 1.2 percent, to
$8,990 a metric ton in London, declining with other commodities
as the dollar advanced.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW) retreated 0.9 percent to 52.35 zloty.
Poland’s largest oil refiner plans to expand its operations in
 Germany  by buying 200 to 250 gas stations, Jozef Niedworok,
chief executive officer at the company’s German unit said at a
conference in Warsaw today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
